{{for|the islets named "Nuku" in Wallis Island|Nuku (disambiguation)#Placenames{{!}}Nuku (disambiguation)}} {{Infobox settlement | name = Nuku | native_name = | other_name = | settlement_type = Village | image_skyline = | image_caption = | pushpin_map = Futuna | pushpin_label_position = right | pushpin_mapsize = 300 | pushpin_map_caption = Location in Futuna Island | coordinates = {{coord|14|17|20.76|S|178|10|0.12|W|region:WF|display=inline,title}} | subdivision_type = Country | subdivision_name = {{flag|France}} | subdivision_type1 = Territory | subdivision_name1 = {{flag|Wallis and Futuna|local}} | subdivision_type2 = Island | subdivision_name2 = [[Futuna (Wallis and Futuna)|Futuna]] | subdivision_type3 = Chiefdom and District | subdivision_name3 = [[Sigave]] | established_title = | established_date = | leader_title = | leader_name = | area_total_km2 = | elevation_footnotes = <ref>[http://www.altitude-maps.com/city/235_18,Nuku,Sigave,Wallis+and+Futuna Infos at altitude-maps.com]</ref> | elevation_m = 6 | elevation_ft = | population_footnotes = | population_total = 267 | population_as_of = 2008 | population_density_km2 = | timezone = [[UTC+12:00|UTC+12]] | utc_offset = | website = | footnotes = }} '''Nuku''' is a village in [[Wallis and Futuna]]. It is located in [[Sigave|Sigave District]] on the northwestern coast of [[Futuna (Wallis and Futuna)|Futuna Island]]. Its population according to the 2008 census was 267 people.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.insee.fr/fr/themes/detail.asp?ref_id=poplegalescom&page=recensement/poplegalescom/popvillwallisetfutuna.htm|title=Population municipale des villages des îles Wallis et Futuna (recensement 2008)|publisher=[[INSEE]]|accessdate=2 September 2013}}</ref>
==Overview== The village lies between [[Leava]], the district seat, and [[Vaisei]]. Its major building is the church of Sausau ({{lang-fr|Eglise de Sausau}}).
